gazooka
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:[Transf. use of a variant name for kazoo, gazoo, a small tubular instrument containing a membrane producing sound when intoned into; first recorded in NZ (as gazoo-zoo) in 1918.] A home-made stringed instrument.
